f nationalism and violence that feed the turmoil there. Forceful, original, and timely, his study combines extensive interview material, historical perspectives, and deep local knowledge. Tishkov sheds light on Chechnya in particular and on how secessionist conflicts can escalate into violent conflagrations in general. With its balanced assessments of both Russian and Chechen perspectives, this book will be essential reading for people seeking to understand the role of Islamic fundamentalist nationalism in the contemporary world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  a1990s.  aacademic.  achechen conflict.  achechnya.  acontemporary world.  adeportation.  aethnographer.  aethnography.  afamily life.  afundamentalist.  agovernment.  ahistorical.  ahostages.  aideology.  aintellectual.  ainternational.  ainterviews.  aislam.  aislamic.  amodern world.  amodernization.  amorals.  amyth.  amythology.  anationalism.  apolitical.  apolitics.  aregional.  areligion.  arevolution.  arussia.  arussian.  ascholarly.  asociology.  aviolence.  awartime.1 aGorbachev, Mikhail S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052023887940uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093020940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520930209423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520930209/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY